membership:
ICCT works with government officials and international experts who are responsible for setting policy to address air pollution and greenhouse gas emissions from the transportation sector. These include government officials from the top vehicle markets in the world which including: European nations (Belgium, UK, Germany), US, China, Canada, Mexico, India, Brazil, and more.&#xd;
In addition, the ICCT is part of a global network of regional philanthropies dedicated to funding the development and implementation of climate and energy policies that lead to significant reductions in carbon emissions.&#xd;
We work closely with the international ClimateWorks Foundation, the European Climate Foundation, the Energy Foundation, and the Energy Foundation China. ICCT is a member of the Climate and Clean Air Coalition to Reduce Short-lived Climate Pollutants (CCC) and the Global Fuel Economy Initiative (GFEI). The ICCT is the Secretariat of the global Zero Emission Vehicle Alliance.
